# Pitch Lock flash landing (intro page)

## Master artwork (source of truth)

- **Canvas:** 2160 × 3840 px, **9∶16**
- **Spec:** `docs/flash-artwork-9x16-spec.md`
- **Designer SVG:** `public/brand/flash-artwork-master-9x16.svg`
- **Safe zone:** 70% × 70% centered — critical content only inside; outer 15% is atmospheric bleed
- **Required in safe zone:** logo, “Pitch. Protect. Progress.”, status labels, Investor Portal, Presenter Portal
- **Display:** `object-fit: contain; object-position: center` — never crop the frame
- **Asset:** `public/brand/pitchlock-flash.mp4` (must match 9∶16 when re-exported)

## Layout code

- Hotspots: `computeContainPortalLayout()` in `flash-portal-hit-layout.ts`
- Media aspect constant: `FLASH_MEDIA_ASPECT = 9/16`
- Re-tune `FLASH_PORTAL_HITS_ON_MEDIA` after final MP4 is locked

## Portal CTA structure (video hotspots only)

- `FlashPortalHotspots` — transparent `<button>` overlays aligned to baked-in portal pills
- Investor: signed → `/dashboard/investor`, else `/nda?next=/dashboard/investor`; Presenter → `/dashboard/presenter`
- Sound toggle is HTML in header, not in the artwork

## Sandbox (do not ship to `/` until finalized)

- Living environment: `/dev/flash-animations` (`FlashLiveEnvironment`)
- Do not wire sandbox experiments into `PitchLockFlashPage` without explicit request

## Do not

- Use `object-fit: cover` on production intro (breaks 9∶16 safe-zone contract)
- Place critical UI in corners of the master frame
- Use gold in artwork
- Check `localStorage === "true"` for signed state; use `hasPitchAccessSignedFlag()`
